<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-28T10:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-28T10:14:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/365.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-28T10:00:00-05:14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 28, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have received from the Minister for Foreign Affairs official
                            information that Dr. Alfredo B. Moreno, President of the Senate arrived
                            in Quito yesterday and has assumed the duties of the Presidency during
                            the absence of President Plaza at Esmeraldas. Matters here have quieted
                            down and the President’s three little sons and nurses have left this
                            Legation and returned to the President’s house. Mrs. Plaza has left the
                            Chilean Legation and is at home.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>